{"id":846069563,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"9 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1668811815,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"218 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/846069563/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"14 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def multiply(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:\n        if num1 == \"0\" or num2 == \"0\":\n            return \"0\"\n            \n        n1 = [int(num) for num in num1[::-1]]\n        n2 = [int(num) for num in num2[::-1]]\n        n, m = len(n1), len(n2)\n        ans = [0] * (n + m)\n        for i in range(n):\n            for j in range(m):\n                pos = i + j\n                curr = n1[i] * n2[j] + ans[pos]\n                ans[pos] = curr % 10\n                ans[pos + 1] += curr // 10\n        while ans[-1] == 0:\n            ans.pop()\n        return \"\".join([str(num) for num in ans[::-1]])\n        ","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
